Very drinkable, One of those beers that stands alone. No need to bother pairing. If pairing is a must I would suggest red meats. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Finish taste is very pleasant. Very nice aroma to go with it. Perfect for advancing your hop recognition in higher IPA's. I believe this is a must before trying the 120IPA. Lovely color as well. Will be purchasing in the near future.  

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Pours to nice a yellow/orange amber with a light head head. Taste notes are hints of dough yeast and citrus malts. The balance of hops and IPA is very pleasant. Don't let the picture on the bottle through you off cause this is a good beer.        

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Pours a dark deep red with little head which fades fast. Malty wood taste, a vary nice taste note would be that of fresh fallin leaves in the fall. Also getting a very peachy/butter scotch after taste which is lovely. All n all a good buy. ---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
